10/08/2008
ANKARA, Turkey -- Turkey's Red Crescent announced on Saturday (August 9th) that it is sending a medical team to the border between Turkey and South Ossetia in an effort to help victims of the armed conflict between Russia and Georgia. The team will work in a field hospital near the Sarp border checkpoint. Turkey also began to supply electricity to Georgia after the country asked Ankara to help it with its energy supplies. (AFP, Cihan, CNN Turk - 09/08/08)
